The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Aug. 16: United Breweries (UB) plans to acquire Scottish distillery Inevrgordon of whisky manufacturer Whyte and Mackay. Though there was no official confirmation of the bid, sources said the offer could be around 200 million (Rs 1,700 crore). The bid for Invergordon is aimed at overcoming opposition from European scotch makers to UBs molasses-based whisky.

 New Delhi, Aug. 16: Bharat Yantra Nigam is likely to be closed down with Board for Reconstruction of Public Enterprises approving a proposal from the department of heavy industries to this effect.

 Mumbai, Aug. 16: The Reserve Bank (RBI) has clarified that NRIs and persons of Indian origin purchasing immovable property in India should pay for the acquisition by funds received in India through normal banking channels by way of inward remittance from outside the country.

 Mumbai, Aug. 16: The maiden offers of GMR Infrastructure and Tech Mahindra will be listed by the end of this month. Tech Mahindra lists on August 29 and GMR Infrastructure lists on August 21. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 16: Corporate houses will have to file annual returns and balance sheets electronically as the registrars of companies will stop accepting these documents in physical form from September 16.




